                    </table>
                    <list>
                        <label>○</label>
                        <item>The <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss> also has converted 800
                            launchers of SS–9s and SS–11s into launchers for SS–17s, SS–18s, and
                            SS–19s. Without <gloss target="#t_SALT_1">SALT</gloss> I the Soviets
                            could have retained the old ICBMs as new ones entered the force.</item>
                        <label>○</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_SALT_1">SALT</gloss> I does not limit heavy bombers.
                            No formal procedures exist for the dismantlement, destruction, or
                            conversion of heavy bombers accountable under <gloss target="#t_SALT_1"
                                >SALT</gloss> II. The <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss> has
                            dismantled 42 B–52s which remain accountable under <gloss
                                target="#t_SALT_1">SALT</gloss> II. The Soviets have converted 2
                            Bison bombers to tankers, and deactivated 35 Bisons, which also remain
                            accountable under <gloss target="#t_SALT_1">SALT</gloss> II.</item>
                    </list>
                </frus:attachment>
